website_summaries.verdict: An all natural treat that provides flavor and variety.
pros: High carb, low fat treats are perfect for young, growing birds, but adults love them, too
Easy to digest snack prevents boredom
Natural spray millet is the only ingredient, no additives
Ideal for budgies, canaries, finches, cockatiels, and more
cons: You may want to store treats elsewhere to keep them fresh

customer_reviews.title: Big waste of money between bad quality and bad packing by Amazon
customer_reviews.text: This product was not fresh and Amazon had packed in a box that was too big with no bubble baffles, with a 5 lb bag of birdseed on top of it. Contents could readily slide around causing further damage. These are fragile sprays of millet seed, they were all smashed and a bunch of seeds had crumbled off the sprays. My birds were really wanting some so I didn't send it back but they actually didn't eat all the seeds off the spray. They looked dried out. There was very little difference from a eaten spray and a non eaten spray. Big waste of money.
customer_reviews.author: Deidre

customer_reviews.title: Beware
customer_reviews.text: I can't be sure but I have been feeding my strawberry finches this this millet for a couple of years. I opened up a new bag and after a few days both my birds are dead. My vet says that sometimes bird food gets contaminated with mycotoxins. Given the other reviews saying that their millet has been moldy I would avoid.
customer_reviews.author: cristi c ludwig

customer_reviews.title: Millet Spray means the seeds shuld be on the spray not in the bottom of the bag
customer_reviews.text: I suppose the millet is fine - however there was lack of proper packaging causing a good portion of the seeds to end up floating around in the bag and not be on the spray of millet. I cut a hole in the bottom of the bag and shook most of the seeds out. The seends are supposed to be on the spray that is the whole point of a spray of millet. My last order was Kaytee brand and there was no problem like this. Also this plastic bag has two air holes and the seeds came out of the air holes and got all other everying else inside the box
customer_reviews.author: Victoria Williams

customer_reviews.title: Great deal, but doesn't get shipped carefully
customer_reviews.text: It's a good price for a good amount of millet. The millet is small, though, so sometimes I give my birds more than one at a time. The only problem with buying this online is that the packagers don't treat it carefully. Both times I ordered it, the other things I ordered were sitting on top of this bag of millet. The result was that there was an inch or more of loose millet sitting on the bottom of the bag. I just poured it into the bird seed and mixed it in.
customer_reviews.author: Sarah L.

customer_reviews.title: if my bird could write a review, he'd give it 5 stars

As soon as he even THINKS I might be giving him a piece of one of these sprays, he's jumping on the side of his cage, yelling as only love birds can, trying to influence me to move faster. And from my side of things: I've had good luck with this product. The sprays are fat and lush, no mold, no insects, and not much loose on the bottom of the bag. product_meta.title: Living World Spray Millet,17.6”.
product_meta.description: Living World Spray Millet is an irresistible treat that will please all companion birds. Nutritious and delicious, the all-natural millet is freshly harvested from the wild and does not contain any additives. Living World Spray Millet is vacuum packed to stay fresh longer, and is ideal for: growing nestlings, young birds, breeding or molting adult birds.
feature_bullets: All Natural, Wholesome Treat For Birds
Harvested From The Wild, No Additives
Treat That Helps Promote Gnawing, Not On The Cage
